ce:section.ce:para:
XPS and FTIR characterizations are performed to study chemical bonds and elemental compositions of N300-CQDs (Fig. 2
                     A). Four XPS peaks at 284.47, 285.82, 287.12 and 288.57 eV are extracted by splitting C1s spectrum, corresponding to CC/CC, CN/CO, CO and COOH groups [27,28], respectively. And three peaks are extracted by splitting N1s spectrum, corresponding to graphitic N, pyrrolic N and pyridinic N (Fig. 2B), respectively. The presence of these functional groups are cross-checked with FTIR characterization (Fig. 2C and Table 1
                     ), in which the absorption peaks centered at 3189, 2933, 1402 and 1075 cm−1 are ascribed to stretching vibration of OH, CH, COC and CO, respectively. Meanwhile, the COOH asymmetric stretching and symmetric stretching modes are determined at 1668 and 1586 cm−1 for N300-CQDs, respectively, and aromatic CH2 rocking is determined at 705 cm−1. Obviously, the basic framework of N300-CQDs comprises of CC bonds, revealing that N300-CQDs have a cyclic aromatic hydrocarbon-like structure for electron transition. Some oxygenic groups such as OH, CH, CO, COC and COOH groups are decorated in in-plane polyaromatic structure or outward surface of N300-CQDs.
